verbs.description: overteem (third-person singular simple present overteems, present participle overteeming, simple past and past participle overteemed)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To be filled or swarming with something.
examples: Yet it was but a dream: yet such a dream / That never tongue, although it overteem / With mellow utterance, like a cavern spring  […]

entries.meaning: To exhaust or deplete by producing excessively.
